(Northbridge Transport Resilience Brief) Tj
T*
(Source ID: northbridge_transport_resilience) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This fictional city brief was created for teaching RAG retrieval and evaluation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Northbridge is a fictional regional transport hub with trams, buses, and a central rail) Tj
T*
(station. Extreme rain, heat, and power disruption are the main climate risks for the network.) Tj
T*
(The most fragile points are Central Underpass, the Riverside tram depot, and the hospital bus) Tj
T*
(corridor.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The transport plan installs new pumps and water sensors at Central Underpass. When water) Tj
T*
(reaches the first warning level, the traffic control room receives an automatic alert. If the) Tj
T*
(second warning level is reached, buses are diverted before cars are trapped. The city wants) Tj
T*
(the underpass closed early rather than late.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For the tram system, Northbridge will raise electrical cabinets at Riverside depot and inspect) Tj
T*
(overhead wires before heat waves. Shade canopies are planned for 18 exposed tram stops. These) Tj
T*
(canopies reduce passenger heat stress and protect ticket machines from direct sun. The city) Tj
T*
(treats passenger safety and equipment reliability as one problem.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Backup bus route B-12 is the core continuity measure. If tram service fails between Riverside) Tj
T*
(depot and the hospital district, B-12 connects the central station, the hospital, and two) Tj
T*
(large housing estates. The route is rehearsed twice per year so drivers know temporary stops) Tj
T*
(before an emergency.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Mobility access is a separate section, not an afterthought. Northbridge requires real-time) Tj
T*
(elevator status at the central station and accessible shuttle vans during major disruptions.) Tj
T*
(The plan says transport resilience fails if wheelchair users, older passengers, and parents) Tj
T*
(with strollers receive information too late to change plans.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The communications team will publish disruption messages in three levels: advisory, service) Tj
T*
(change, and emergency closure. Messages must name the affected line, the reason, the expected) Tj
T*
(duration if known, and the accessible alternative. The plan avoids vague phrases such as) Tj
T*
(severe weather disruption without practical instructions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The first-year budget is 5.1 million city credits. The main success measures are fewer) Tj
T*
(weather-related service hours lost, faster underpass closure decisions, and better passenger) Tj
T*
(satisfaction during disruptions. Northbridge expects some service interruptions to remain, but) Tj
T*
(it wants them to be shorter, clearer, and less dangerous.) Tj
T*
() Tj
